	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>k i got one of these its fun its off hand usuable since the delay is too high for a warrior to really taunt with at the top end of the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its a 45 point life tap proc yes it can be used with boon..however boon taps dont "stack" with weapon procs.  Boon taps are thier own independant proc i think the proc for a booned player is round 37 or 38 at lvl 60 i forget now its been a while since i was booned.  <br><br>This weapon is obviously a bard weapon if you have a bard in group..its not low enough delay to taunt much the proc isnt a monster taunt either after all its only a 45 pt tap and basically bards dont get so many weapons like this.<br><br>It drops off "a failed experiment" who rampages an awful lot but we took him with one group, me tanking and using defencive discipline and the enchanter throwing a rune my way ever time i got down round 1.5 bubs of health giving cleric time to ch.  He max hit me fer like 185 with disc but mostly low hundreds so he wasnt that harsh.<br><br>I suppose a rogue might find some use for this thing in his off hand but honestly..theres a bundle of far superior options out there. Especially if they are of the correct level to be taking this thing out with one group (56+), also an sk wouldnt touch this with a 10 foot pole its no drop and no sk in his right mind is gonna use a 10 dmg 1 hander in his high 50's and as its no great leap for a warrior theres so much more out there then this.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>-------THIS IS A MONK ITEM!!! YES!!!!--------</td></tr>
